PART 2: INFRASTRUCTURE AND BINARIES (RESTRICTED USE)
===============================================================================

The following components have more restrictive terms:

1. Binary executables (relay-linux-*, relay-macos-*, relay-win-*.exe)
2. Installation scripts (install.sh, install.ps1)
3. Core platform files - Any code that implements the Relay platform functionality

Terms for Infrastructure Components:

- **Use**: You may use these components for personal and commercial purposes
- **Distribution**: You may distribute unmodified copies
- **Modification**: You may NOT modify, reverse-engineer, or create derivative works
- **Redistribution of Modified Versions**: Strictly prohibited
- **Commercial Use**: Permitted only for unmodified official versions

===============================================================================
PART 3: CONTRIBUTION GUIDELINES
===============================================================================

Allowed Contributions:
- Add new clips to store.json
- Add assets for your clips in assets/clips/
- Improve documentation
- Report bugs and suggest features

Prohibited Actions:
- Modify binary executables
- Modify installation scripts
- Modify core platform files
- Distribute modified versions of binaries
- Use modified binaries commercially

